International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Wed 19 Jan 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: WHO Outbreak Reports [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2005_01_19/en/print.html>

Typhoid fever in the Democratic Republic of the Congo - update
-----------------------------------------------
From 27 Sep 2004 - 11 Jan 2005, WHO has received reports of a total of 42
564 cases and 214 deaths (case fatality ratio, 0.5 percent), and 696 severe
cases of intestinal perforation in Kinshasa.
Medecins sans Frontieres-Belgium has been working to provide clean water.
With this provision and other control measures, including health education
activities, the number of cases appears to be declining.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[It is encouraging to hear that this large outbreak of typhoid fever may be
abating. - Mod.LL]
